  "prompt": "Which is best digital marketing course?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" digital marketing course can be subjective and dependent on your specific needs, goals, and current skill level. However, here are some highly regarded options:\n\n1. **Google Digital Garage**: Offers free courses on various aspects of digital marketing including search engine optimization (SEO), social media marketing, and web analytics.\n\n2. **HubSpot Academy**: Provides comprehensive free courses covering inbound marketing, content marketing, email marketing, and more. Offers certification upon completion.\n\n3. **Coursera's Digital Marketing Specialization by the University of Illinois**: This is a paid, more in-depth series of courses covering various aspects of digital marketing, culminating in a capstone project.\n\n4. **Facebook Blueprint**: Free courses specifically focused on using Facebook's suite of tools and platforms for marketing.\n\n5. **LinkedIn Learning**: Offers a breadth of courses focused on various aspects of digital marketing and social media strategy, taught by industry professionals.\n\n6. **Udemy**: Includes a large selection of digital marketing courses ranging from beginner to advanced levels. Popular courses are often on sale and taught by practitioners in the field.\n\n7. **Simplilearn**: Comprehensive programs including Master's programs and certificates in partnership with Purdue University and the Digital Marketing Institute.\n\n8. **Digital Marketing Institute (DMI)**: Offers professional certifications that are globally recognized. Programs range from diploma to postgraduate levels.\n\nWhen evaluating a digital marketing course, consider factors such as the comprehensiveness of the curriculum, the credentials of the instructors, the format (online/self-paced vs. classroom), and reviews from past participants. Try to match the course content to your career goals and current skill set to get the most benefit from your investment.",
